Enum JMessage.Port

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<JMessage.Port>
      • io.odysz.semantic.jprotocol.JMessage.Port
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IPort, Serializable, Comparable<JMessage.Port>
    Enclosing class:
    JMessage<T extends JBody>

    public static enum JMessage.Port
extends Enum<JMessage.Port>
implements IPort
    Port is the conceptual equivalent to the SOAP port, the service methods' group.
    NOTE: java code shouldn't use switch-case block on enum. That cause problem with generated class. TODO shall we use dynamic registered ports?
    Author:
    odys-z@github.com
